asset_contract.name: FLUF
asset_contract.description:
This is FLUF World…

A metaverse ecosystem of NFT character collectables and a global, creative community. From our genesis collection Flufs, to Thingies, Party Bears and more to come, we’re building a world that’s yours to shape, explore and call home. 

Flufs are the collection that started it all. 10,000 3D rabbit avatars, programmatically-generated from over 270 traits! Unique by at least three degrees of separation, Flufs are yours to trade, collect and customise through our growing Scenes & Sounds collection. 

But Flufs aren’t just furry faces... Metaverse-ready and full of surprises, they’re your ticket to a world of exclusive content, digital connectivity, IRL experiences and more.

Welcome to the Fluffle. 

---

**Official Collections:**

[FLUF World: Thingies](https://opensea.io/collection/fluf-world-thingies)

[FLUF World: Burrows](https://opensea.io/collection/fluf-world-burrows)

[FLUF World: Scenes & Sounds](https://opensea.io/collection/fluf-world-scenes-and-sounds)

name: Black Velvet
description: Have you seen her? Probably not. She has the unique ability to meld into the darkness and strangely, the brighter the conditions, the darker she gets. A chameleon of sorts, that unknown figure slipping quietly away into a fluffle. Was that really a Fluf? Black Velvet is the epitome of professional, as a spy she is slyer than a fox and more mysterious than the underground at night. Just like her peer over in Gotham City, Bruce Wayne, Black Velvet is one of the most well known yet unknown figures of the underground.  Social, charismatic and well spoken, yet nothing is known of her private life.  Depending on your allegiance, you have either a worst enemy or your best friend this Fluf. To put it simply, she knows. With eyes that can penetrate your thoughts for a non verbal confession, or a gaze capable of making one temporarily insane, you will never know if she has been inside your mind until it is too late.  Black Velvet works as an invisible force to be reckoned with. She saved unknown numbers of FLUF during The Wreck and has since been a long time friend of Scrooge McFluf. Operating above the law, she has been entrusted to keep Fluf world safe. Whether that be by securing digital currency, mas saging politics, disrupting daily life, her main code is to ensure the spreading of good vibes only.  Although you may not see her, you will know if she is in your vicinity as you will be literally shaking without knowing why.  Maybe she is reading your thoughts already.  Best be a good minded Fluf then, malicious intent is her pet hate. You have been warned.

name: Cernunnos
description:
Little is known about is origins.
Cernunnos (The horned Fluf) didn't born with Horns. They grew after a long relationship with a religious woman. She was so often unfaithful that the horns grew and took root all the way to the inside of the brain.

He likes to be surrounded by beings that live in the underworld. 
It is said  that he can heal with just the touch of his aura. Many other tales were told about him. In the present times there are still sites that tell these tales.
He has been seen with wild bulls and loves spiders for company since young age. For he was born and raised in lands with beauty and wealth of wild life.

A metaverse ecosystem of NFT character collectables and a global, creative community. From our genesis collection Flufs, to Thingies, Party Bears and more to come, we’re building a world that’s yours to shape, explore and call home. 

Flufs are the collection that started it all. 10,000 3D rabbit avatars, programmatically-generated from over 270 traits! Unique by at least three degrees of separation, Flufs are yours to trade, collect and customise through our growing Scenes & Sounds collection. 

But Flufs aren’t just furry faces... Metaverse-ready and full of surprises, they’re your ticket to a world of exclusive content, digital connectivity, IRL experiences and more.

Welcome to the Fluffle. 

---

name: Bandhani
description: Bandhani (Hindi: बांधानी) is a type of tie-dye textile decorated by plucking the cloth with the fingernails into many tiny bindings that form a figurative design.The term bandhani is derived from the Sanskrit verbal root bandh (“to bind, to tie”). Today most Bandhani making centers are situated in Gujarat, Rajasthan, Sindh, Punjab region and in Tamil Nadu where it’s known as Sungudi. Earliest evidence of Bandhani dates back to Indus Valley Civilization where dyeing was done as early as 4000 B.C. The earliest example of the most pervasive type of Bandhani dots can be seen in the 6th century paintings depicting the life of Buddha found on the wall of Cave 1 at Ajanta. Bandhani is also known as Bandhej, Bandhni, Piliya, and Chungidi in Tamil and regional dialects. Other tying techniques include Mothra, Ekdali and Shikari depending on the manner in which the cloth is tied. The final products are known with various names including Khombi, Ghar Chola, Patori and Chandrokhani.
